Recall that our search has identified 49 primary studies that have applied unsupervised learning to the task of software defect prediction. These are published over the period of 2000-2018 [W2611052873] and are summarised in Table 5 and also by Figure 1. From this we can see that conference papers tend to dominate and that there has been pronounced growth in the overall number of papers published in recent years as indicated by the smoother in Figure 1.

